-- E14 / EMITTER-GAPS #14 (non-Int literal switch): a Char-literal match head.
-- Char is an immediate codepoint word (cp << 1) | 1, so the emitLitChain arm for
-- `HLit (LChar _)` is the same icmp-eq shape as Int — but the head still reaches
-- the previously-unhandled non-Int branch.  The first arm ('a') falls through to
-- the second ('b'), proving chain order on a Char column.
main = match 'b'
  'a' => 1
  'b' => 2
  _ => 0
